org.apache.lens.server.api.query.collect

Interface ImmutableQueryCollection

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    EstimatedImmutableQueryCollection, EstimatedQueryCollection, QueryCollection
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultEstimatedQueryCollection, DefaultQueryCollection, ThreadSafeEstimatedQueryCollection, ThreadSafeQueryCollection

    public interface ImmutableQueryCollection
    ImmutableQueryCollection interface defines immutable behaviours on queries existing in lens system.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Set<QueryContext> getQueries() 
      Set<QueryContext> getQueries(String user) 
      int getQueriesCount() 

    • Method Detail

      • getQueries

        Set<QueryContext> getQueries()
        Returns:
        A new set copied from this collection of queries. Elements in the set are not cloned or copied. Multiple iterations over returned set are guaranteed to be in same order. If there are no queries, then an empty set is returned. null is never returned.

      • getQueries

        Set<QueryContext> getQueries(String user)
        Parameters:
        user - User for whom queries have to be returned.
        Returns:
        A set of queries submitted by the given user. A new set is created and returned. Elements in the set are not cloned or copied. Multiple iterations over returned set are guaranteed to be in same order. If there are no queries, then an empty set is returned. null is never returned.

      • getQueriesCount

        int getQueriesCount()
        Returns:
        Count of existing queries
